    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/d38912b59f97a4da0a2d0a24af226e6dd27e9b2c introduced a regression where `wrap` (and other local options) are set window-scoped instead of locally.\r\nThis is a problem because if the user then opens up a new buffer in the same window then `wrap` (and other local options) will be incorrectly set.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:set wrap? \"reporst `wrap`\r\n:term\r\n:enew\r\n:set wrap? \"should report `wrap`, but reports `nowrap`\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`wrap` should be set locally instead of window-scoped.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-f75053a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux 6.9.4-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.35.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
